 the late John O Crown and Joseph W Crown for more thun 84 years Entered at the Postofflce at lierry fllle Vu as secondclsss mail ttnt ter 50 Per Year In Advance EMERGENCY CROPS FOR STOCK FEED The Commission on Drought Re lief has received so many Inquiries as to what farmers can do t meet the feed shortage that the chairman has requested Director John Hutcheson member of the commit tee to prepare a special statement on Sis subject Mr Hutcheson has consulted the members agron omy department of the Virginia E periment Station and makes the following statement Owing to the lateness if the sea ion there is little hope that any crop may be seeded after this date witS the certainitytha arop fQOf forage may aggured would have an abundance of ram and that frost would not come earl ier than the average frost date we might still sow such crops as millet buckwheat and early soybeans but August and September are normally months of light rainfall nothing but a very unusual sueasn Uabove sure sufficient"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-09-28T23:53:50.775Z", "group": ["ndnp/vi", "library-of-virginia-richmond-va-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85025371/1930-08-28/ed-1/?sp=4", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_moser_ver01:data:sn85025371:00542867322:1930082801:0700/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=467&w=317", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_moser_ver01:data:sn85025371:00542867322:1930082801:0700/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=934&w=635", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/vi/batch_vi_moser_ver01/data/sn85025371/00542867322/1930082801/0700.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["virginia", "berryville", "clarke", "clarke county", "united states"], "location_city": ["berryville"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["clarke"], "location_state": ["virg